au.edu.rmit.tzar.api

Class Repetitions

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.rmit.tzar.api.Repetitions

  • public class Repetitions
extends java.lang.Object
    Class to hold repetitions definition. A repetitions object contains a list of Parameters object, each one of which represents one repetition. For that repetition, the parameters in that Parameter object override the parameters given by the scenario, project spec or global spec.

    • Method Detail

      • getParamsList

        public java.util.List<Parameters> getParamsList()
                                         throws TzarException
        Gets the list of Parameters (where each parameters object itself represents a list of parameters) for the repetitions defined by this object. The list of Parameters is generated by computing the cartesian product of: the set of "static" repetitions held by this object and the set of all repetitions generated by all of the generators held by this object.
        Returns:
        a list of Parameters objects
        Throws:
        TzarException
